documentation.text:
@dev Cast a vote
 Emits a {VoteCast} event.

@dev Execute a successful proposal. This requires the quorum to be reached, the vote to be successful, and the
 deadline to be reached.
 Emits a {ProposalExecuted} event.
 Note: some module can modify the requirements for execution, for example by adding an additional timelock.

@notice module:voting
 @dev Returns weither `account` has cast a vote on `proposalId`.

@notice module:core
 @dev Current state of a proposal, following Compound's convention

castVote(uint256,uint8).details: Cast a vote Emits a {VoteCast} event.

execute(address[],bytes[],bytes32).details: Execute a successful proposal. This requires the quorum to be reached, the vote to be successful, and the deadline to be reached. Emits a {ProposalExecuted} event. Note: some module can modify the requirements for execution, for example by adding an additional timelock.

hasVoted(uint256,address).details: Returns weither `account` has cast a vote on `proposalId`.

propose(address[],bytes[],string).details: Create a new proposal. Vote start {IGovernor-votingDelay} blocks after the proposal is created and ends {IGovernor-votingPeriod} blocks after the voting starts. Emits a {ProposalCreated} event.

queue(address[],bytes[],bytes32).details: Move the successfully voted proposal (Succeeded) to the pending execution queue

state(uint256).details: Current state of a proposal, following Compound's convention
